title: For Sale:  Savage 212 with Upgrades
postcontent: This is a savage 212 100% ready to hunt right out of the box - all you need is shells. this is Savage's 12 gauge version of their dedicated slug gun in a bolt action platform as to increase accuracy. Shoots 2 3/4", 3", or 3 1/2" remington sabot slugs like a dream. I have personally pulled the trigger on 9 deer and all 9 were dead on the spot with a hole bigger than necessary. This gun comes with a nikon slughunter scope with steel rings and its all been blue locktighted because of the heavy recoil of the slugs. Rifled slug guns also have a tendency to "jump" and twist to the left when you shoot them - so I had mine "magnaported" look it up if you are unfamiliar. Its a process of porting the barrel using a laser ($165) - doing this has completely gotten rid of muzzle jump without damaging the rifling in the barrel - now it recoils straight back as any other rifle would. Also includes an extra heavy duty recoil pad for those days when you want to shoot more comfortably. If you were to buy all of this new, not including the gunsmith time I paid for - even though it has the magnaport ($165), the nikon 3-9 slughunter ($179.99), steel rings from badger ordnance ($110), recoil pad ($35). In all, I have put in $489 worth of upgrades. Check out the pics for closeups of the magnaporting. Will ship to FFL, buyer pays actual ground shipping costs.

title: For Sale:  (REDUCED PRICE) Kar 98 az not Kar98K (Has Battle Damage)
postcontent: A Great piece of history, This is a 1916 Enfurt Kar 98 az Used by the Imperial German Army during The Great War. This Rifle was primarly used by second line Troops until around late 1916 when SturmTroopers got their hands on them and thrusted them into the front lines. This Rifle is Not All Matching but has a good bore and strong rifling and still has its Rack Numbers on the stock. This Rifle was most likely used by a SturmTrooper and saw the damage on the Handguard from a bullet or piece of sharpnel while it and the soldier carrying it were Assaulting a Trench. This is an Amazing piece of history, though the rifle might not be in the best condition it is still in good condition for a 100 year old rifle that has seen combat.Cash Only. (If you are interested or want more info Just Text or Call me at REDACTED)Local only not shipping.
